<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880126-0098 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News: Bessemer's Cardwell Is Named to 3 Posts </HL><SO> </SO><CO> WNEWS </CO><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Bessemer Securities Corp., a private investment company, said John J. Cardwell, executive vice president, was named president, chief executive officer and a director.    Mr. Cardwell succeeds Paul Bancroft III, who retired but will serve as a consultant to the concern, whose main business is acquiring and managing companies for its own account.    Mr. Cardwell, 57 years old, came to Bessemer in 1983 from Sara Lee Corp., the food concern, where he was president and chief operating officer. Mr. Cardwell was also elected a director of affiliated Bessemer Trust Co., an asset management concern that serves high-net-worth individuals and institutions.    Bessemer Securities is owned by descendants of Henry Phipps, who was a partner of Andrew Carnegie in Carnegie Steel Co. </TEXT></DOC>